    "created_at": "2015-07-26T09:50:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-26T09:50:53Z",
    "body": "To respond to your comment in the other thread. I don't agree with the unusefulness of allowing arbitrary page size. Although \"export to pdf\" rather than \"print to pdf\" would better describe what I want to do, I think it would be great to be able to reuse the code you have written. Just a few examples when arbitrary sized pdf would be necessary:\n- If you use something like [reveal.js](https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js) for creating presentations you might want to export pdf files sized to fit the screen.\n- To create vector images that can be included in pdf files created by typesetting programs like latex.\n\nI played a little with this last night by trying to adjust sizes in `atom/browser/api/lib/web-contents.coffee` but I had trouble converting pixel dimensions to metric dimensions. Also, I don't have any knowledge about the chromium printing api. Is there any reference or documentation available for it?\n"
  },
